239. Sliding Window Maximum

You are given an array of integers nums, there is a sliding window of size k which is moving from the very left of the array to the very right.
You can only see the k numbers in the window. Each time the sliding window moves right by one position.

Return the max sliding window.

Example 1:

Input: nums = [1,3,-1,-3,5,3,6,7], k = 3
Output: [3,3,5,5,6,7

// Optimal Appraoch
class Solution
{
    public int[] maxSlidingWindow(int[] nums, int k)
    {
        // Deque to store elements in decreasing order (max at front)
        ArrayDeque<Integer> q = new ArrayDeque<>(); 
        
        int i = 0;      // Left pointer of window
        int j = 0;      // Right pointer of window
        int ptr = 0;    // Pointer to store result index
        
        int n = nums.length; // Length of input array
        
        // Result array of size (n - k + 1)
        int[] res = new int[n - k + 1]; 

        // Traverse the array using sliding window
        while (j < n)
        {
            // Remove all smaller elements from the back of deque
            // because they cannot be maximum if current element is larger
            while (!q.isEmpty() && q.peekLast() < nums[j])
            {
                q.pollLast(); // Remove smaller elements
            }
        
            // Add current element to deque
            q.add(nums[j]);

            // If window size is smaller than k, just expand window
            if (j - i + 1 < k)
            {
                j++; 
            }
            // When window size becomes exactly k
            else if (j - i + 1 == k)
            {
                // The front of deque is the maximum of current window
                res[ptr++] = q.peek();
                
                // If the element going out of window is equal to max
                // remove it from deque
                if (nums[i] == q.peek())
                {
                    q.pollFirst(); 
                }

                // Slide the window forward
                i++; 
                j++;
            }
        }

        // Return result array
        return res; 
    }
}

| Type             | Value                       |
| ---------------- | --------------------------- |
| Time Complexity  | **O(n)** ✅                  |
| Space Complexity | **O(n)** (including result) |


class Solution {
    public int[] maxSlidingWindow(int[] nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int[] res = new int[n - k + 1];
        int idx = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i <= n - k; i++) {
            int max = nums[i];

            for (int j = i; j < i + k; j++) {
                if (nums[j] > max) {
                    max = nums[j];
                }
            }

            res[idx++] = max;
        }

        return res;
    }
}

| Approach          | Time   | Space | Idea                    |
| ----------------- | ------ | ----- | ----------------------- |
| Brute Force       | O(n·k) | O(n)  | Check each window       |
| Optimal (Deque) ✅ | O(n)   | O(k)  | Remove useless elements |
